						<p class="journal">Catena 250, 108774</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Hydrology</span>
							<span class="tag">Streamflow</span>
							<span class="tag">Yangtze River</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>150-year daily data (1870–2021) in lakes and rivers reveals intensifying surface water warming and heatwaves in the Pannonian Ecoregion (Hungary)</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2024</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors"><strong>Li, H.</strong>, Sun, J., Zhou, Q., Sojka, M., Ptak, M., Luo, Y., Wu, S., Zhu, S. and Tóth, V.R.</p>
						<p class="journal">Journal of Hydrology: Regional Studies 56, 101985</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Water Temperature</span>
							<span class="tag">Climate Change</span>
							<span class="tag">Pannonian Region</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>Exploring spatiotemporal features of surface water temperature for Lake Balaton in the 21st century based on Google Earth Engine</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2024</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors"><strong>Li, H.</strong>, Sun, J., Zhou, Q., Sojka, M., Ptak, M., Luo, Y., Wu, S., Zhu, S. and Tóth, V.R.</p>
						<p class="journal">Journal of Hydrology 640, 131672</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Remote Sensing</span>
							<span class="tag">Google Earth Engine</span>
							<span class="tag">Lake Balaton</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>Exploring the topographical pattern beneath the water surface: Global Bathymetric Volume-Area-Height curves (BVAH) of inland surface water bodies</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2024</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors">Zhu, S., Wan, W., Zhang, G., …, and <strong>Li, H.</strong></p>
						<p class="journal">Geodesy and Geodynamics</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Bathymetry</span>
							<span class="tag">Inland Waters</span>
							<span class="tag">Global Analysis</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>Inspects and prospects of satellite remote sensing monitoring ability for land surface water in China</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2023</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors"><strong>Li, H.</strong>, Wan, W., Zeng, C., Hong, Y.</p>
						<p class="journal">National Remote Sensing Bulletin 27</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Remote Sensing</span>
							<span class="tag">Surface Water</span>
							<span class="tag">China</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>A remote sensing-based area dataset for approximately 40 years that reveals the hydrological asynchrony of Lake Chad based on Google Earth Engine</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2021</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors"><strong>Li, H.</strong>, Wan, W., Zeng, C., Hong, Y.</p>
						<p class="journal">Journal of Hydrology 603, 126934</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Lake Chad</span>
							<span class="tag">Hydrology</span>
							<span class="tag">Google Earth Engine</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>Improving the Evapotranspiration Estimation under Cloudy Condition by Extending the Ts-VI Triangle Model</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2021</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors">Li, B., Cui, Y., Geng, X. and <strong>Li, H.</strong></p>
						<p class="journal">Remote Sensing 13(8), 1516</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Evapotranspiration</span>
							<span class="tag">Remote Sensing</span>
							<span class="tag">Modeling</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>Distribution and Attribution of Terrestrial Snow Cover Phenology Changes over the Northern Hemisphere during 2001–2020</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2021</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors">Chen, X., Yang, Y., Ma, Y. and <strong>Li, H.</strong></p>
						<p class="journal">Remote Sensing 13(9), 1843</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Snow Cover</span>
							<span class="tag">Phenology</span>
							<span class="tag">Climate Change</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>Decadal variations of sea ice thickness in the Amundsen-Bellingshausen and Weddell Seas retrieved from ICESat and IceBridge laser altimetry, 2003-2017</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2020</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors">Wang, X., Jiang, W., Xie, H., Ackley, S. and <strong>Li, H.</strong></p>
						<p class="journal">Journal of Geophysical Research: Oceans 125(12), e2020JC016077</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Sea Ice</span>
							<span class="tag">ICESat</span>
							<span class="tag">Antarctic</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="publications-section">
				<h2>Book Chapters</h2>
				<div class="publication-list">
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>Dynamic correlation analysis of the stock markets of China and United States based on big financial system data</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2017</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors">Shi, W., <strong>Li, H.</strong>, Hong, Y.</p>
						<p class="journal">In "Practical Case Study of Big Data in Financial Industry," Editor Liu, S. Economic Science Press: 145-164 (In Chinese)</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Big Data</span>
							<span class="tag">Financial Analysis</span>
							<span class="tag">Stock Markets</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="publications-section">
				<h2>Conference Proceedings</h2>
				<div class="publication-list">
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>Retrieving chlorophyll-a concentration for lake Balaton with Landsat based on Google Earth Engine</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2023</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors"><strong>Li, H.</strong>, Blix, K., Somogyi, B., Tóth, V.R., et al.</p>
						<p class="journal">IEEE Geoscience and Remote Sensing Symposium (IGARSS)</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Chlorophyll-a</span>
							<span class="tag">Landsat</span>
							<span class="tag">Lake Balaton</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>Ship Navigation Route Planning Using Topology of Sea Ice Channels Extracted from High Resolution Satellite Images</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2020</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors">Chen, X., Sheti, W., <strong>Li, H.</strong>, et al.</p>
						<p class="journal">IEEE Geoscience and Remote Sensing Symposium (IGARSS)</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Sea Ice</span>
							<span class="tag">Navigation</span>
							<span class="tag">Satellite Images</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>A Remote Sensing-based Vacancy Area Index for Estimating Housing Vacancy and Ghost Cities in China</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2019</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors"><strong>Li, H.</strong>, Zeng, C., Wan, W., Hong, Y., et al.</p>
						<p class="journal">IEEE International Geoscience and Remote Sensing Symposium (IGARSS)</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Urban Analysis</span>
							<span class="tag">Housing Vacancy</span>
							<span class="tag">China</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					
					<div class="publication-card">
						<div class="pub-header">
							<h3>Can Crowdsourcing Support Remote Sensing Image Classification?</h3>
							<span class="pub-year">2018</span>
						</div>
						<p class="authors"><strong>Li, H.</strong>, Zeng, C., Wan, W., Hong, Y., et al.</p>
						<p class="journal">The 26th International Conference on GeoInformatics</p>
						<div class="pub-tags">
							<span class="tag">Crowdsourcing</span>
							<span class="tag">Image Classification</span>
							<span class="tag">Remote Sensing</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.page-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 3em;
		padding: 2em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
	}

	.page-header h1 {
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}

	.page-subtitle {
		font-size: 1.2em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		margin: 0;
		font-style: italic;
	}

	.metrics {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5em;
		margin: 3em 0;
	}

	.metric-card {
		padding: 2em;
		text-align: center;
		background: white;
		border-radius: 12px;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
		transition: transform 0.2s;
	}

	.metric-card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-5px);
	}

	.metric-number {
		display: block;
		font-size: 2.5em;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--accent);
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}

	.metric-label {
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		font-size: 1em;
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.publications-section {
		margin: 4em 0;
		padding: 2em 0;
	}

	.publications-section:first-of-type {
		margin-top: 0;
	}

	.publications-section h2 {
		margin-bottom: 2em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
		font-size: 1.8em;
	}

	.publication-list {
		display: grid;
		gap: 2em;
	}

	.publication-card {
		padding: 2em;
		background: white;
		border-radius: 12px;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
		border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
		transition: transform 0.2s;
	}

	.publication-card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-3px);
	}

	.pub-header {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: flex-start;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
		gap: 1em;
	}

	.pub-header h3 {
		margin: 0;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
		font-size: 1.2em;
		line-height: 1.4;
		flex: 1;
	}

	.pub-year {
		background: var(--accent);
		color: white;
		padding: 0.3em 0.8em;
		border-radius: 15px;
		font-size: 0.85em;
		font-weight: 600;
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.authors {
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin: 0.5em 0;
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.journal {
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		font-style: italic;
		margin: 0.5em 0;
		font-size: 0.95em;
	}

	.pub-tags {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.5em;
		margin-top: 1em;
	}

	.tag {
		background: rgb(var(--gray-light));
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		padding: 0.3em 0.8em;
		border-radius: 15px;
		font-size: 0.8em;
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.metrics {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
			gap: 1em;
		}

		.metric-card {
			padding: 1.5em;
		}

		.metric-number {
			font-size: 2em;
		}

		.pub-header {
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: flex-start;
		}

		.pub-year {
			align-self: flex-start;
		}

		.publication-card {
			padding: 1.5em;
		}

		.page-header {
			padding: 1em 0;
			margin-bottom: 2em;
		}

		.publications-section {
			margin: 2em 0;
			padding: 1em 0;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 480px) {
		.metrics {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
